20 Nov 2018 14:46






Fair enough! The hardest decisions I took on this were a) how much detail of the detail I worked out about the plant's reproductive cycle to include and b) whether it needed more of a payoff in the ending than it now has; I could very easily have decided differently but in the end went with the version that got the most positive reviews from my reviewers.

I might spin off some of my cutting room floor ideas into a tale or something, or maybe, if a bunch of people are finding the ending to lack payoff, I'll edit the skip itself. But I'm going to let it sit for a bit before I do either.

I appreciate you holding feet to the fire in quality terms though shaggydredlocks , we can always be better, and there's not much point in writing here if I'm not being pushed to improve.







